changes:
	Jamfile added to build TUT Framework using
	Boost Build System V2.
	It builds and automatically executes TUT selftest. If build is successfull the TUT version is correct. Further enchancements will coming soon.

	New functionality added: at now TUT users can optionally specify a test name inside the test.

    template < > template < > 
    void my_object_tests::test < 1 > () 
    { 
        // specify test name set_test_name("test basic scenario"); 
        // test code 
        // ... 
    }
	If test fails and the test name was specified as above, the test name will appear in the test report, i.e.:

    ---> group: my_object, test: test<1> : test basic scenario 
         problem: assertion failed 
	     failed assertion: "not implemented"

	Also if you write your own custom reporter you can retrieve a test name from tut::test_result::name member.

	Minor fix: TUT selftest doesn't return 0 longer if there were failed tests.
